def: A pouring out; an outburst.A passionate outgush of emotion. Thackeray.
A large tub or vat in which goods are subjected to the actionof hot lye or bleaching liquor; -- also called keeve.
A coarse umbelliferous plant of Europe (Tordylium maximum).
An instrument designed for transmitting pictures by telegraph.Fallows.
Pertaining to a Presbyterian consistory; -- a contemptuous termof 17th century controversy.You fall next on the consistorian schismatics; for so you callPresbyterians. Milton.
Pertaining to, or designating, an acid produced artifically asa white crystalline substance, CH2.(CO2H)2, and so called becauseobtained by the oxidation of malic acid.
The broad-billed singing birds, such as the swallows, and theirallies.
Of or pertaining to a siphon.
